Scope\">13.827</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τάων μοι περὶ κῆρι τιέσκετο Ἴλιος ἱρή</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:46\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.46</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>: esp. <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\">pf.</tns> <mood opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"mood\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ part.\">part.</a></mood> <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"voice\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pass.\">Pass.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τετιμένος</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">honoured</tr_>, of persons, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">οὔτε θεοῖσι τετιμένος οὔτε βροτοῖσιν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:24:533\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">24.533</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0020.tlg001.perseus-grc1:415\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hes.\">Hes.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Th.\">Th.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">415</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λαοῖσι τ</foreign>. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:13:28\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">13.28</biblScope></bibl>, etc.:—also in Trag. (never in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> </bibl>), but only <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ pres.\">pres.</a></tns> and <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ impf.\">impf.</a></tns> in this sense, the other tenses being supplied from <cit TEIform=\"cit\